column4: I feel like I have been rebuilding my entire main line today ;)
and you are ok? i got tons of desync with windows. i dont know why.
are you using GDI or SDL?
I am using GDI, I think fewer desyncs
i restarted it to linux version and now it is ok. much fewer desync.
what happens with your main line?
Oh, I've just been rebuilding many of the interchanges
so that I can move more trains
I'm running maybe 30 trains/month/direction on a slow freight line with many entrance points
ok. unlike you, i have just removed some trains ;)
If I remove trains then I won't haul enough freight...
If I recall, this is about 2 am your time?
hmm looks like we have slower line compared to north and south.
yes 2am here. but tomorrow is free.
Ah. 3pm here. Yes, very few new industries in east and west as compared to north and south
oh you are the same rf&p as it was.
btw thanks for the books and cars.
no problem. I've been trying to capitalize on exports since not much industry here
however i still have 1 electronic factory. but i'm to lazy to work on it.
If you want meat for the other food factory, I can bring that once G can haul from cowser
ah thanks for reminding me. i almost forget to work with it.
I will send, but SCNFS must have a train too.
I will put a note for him at the opening screen
let me see. which public station will you send it?
green doesn't have fridge train there.
I will set up my part of the chain and you can set up yours so It will work when G returns
btw do you like some party? we have a lot of beer here in knitten.
haha. no beer here in the east ;)
Once on gift. prissi made a city called "nobeerhere"
and there was a public interchange in this city
haha... must be a long time ago.
So I put up a 'billboard' advertising that there was beer at the city my trains went to ;)
it must be fun if the server automaticly create brewery in that city.
sorry. my internet connection suddenly goes crazy.
is there any way to see the origin of things?
Generally no, but where do you want to know?
Oh, crap, just jammed the mainline
Yes, there was a reason I didn't put a signal there...
I put a signal in a bad place and jammed the trains
ok. i did that a few times here too.
Can you look at the new rail interchange at the Outsbruck steel mill and make sure it won't jam?
as long as the 5 tiles train not stop at 616 237
good. now the mainline between blackrock and mascow should be up to high capacity
that is onlu for outbound steel trains to the car factory
i can see. it is a busy line
ok no problem than. just be carefull.
stuff looks like going everywhere it likes to.
Well, it can be controlled, but G's network in particular sends some goods on odd routes, resulting in stockpiles
yes i have to modify my station for it.
my electronic factory has 3 unconnected station.
Yes, and if there are connections to all three, goods will go to all three!
G share some meat to the food factory we talked before.
so the factory can produce food while we are waiting G to connect to your factory.
i know but i can use it while waiting for him.
Once you have enough meat, you will need that track to be faster, I think
the supermarket can consume over 2000 units of food per month
yes this one consume 2036 crates per month
